        <briefdescription>
<para>Serialize an HTML node to a memory, also returning the size of the result. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>It&apos;s up to the caller to free the memory.</para>
<para>Uses the encoding of the document. If the document has no encoding, ASCII with HTML 4.0 named character entities will be used. This is inefficient compared to UTF-8 and might be changed in a future version.</para>
